<h2>TikTok – The Most Popular Short Video Platform in the World</h2>

<p>
TikTok is one of the fastest-growing social media platforms in the world. It allows users to create, watch, and share short videos ranging from a few seconds to a few minutes.
</p>

<p>
The platform was launched in 2016 by a company called ByteDance. Later it merged with Musical.ly and became global.
</p>

<p>
TikTok uses a powerful algorithm called “For You Page (FYP)” which shows videos based on user interest.
</p>

<p>
People also earn money from TikTok through brand deals, creator fund, and live gifts.
</p>

